N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 326-1.2 - Application for license to operate medical bureau or laboratory

State Regulations

Applications for licenses to operate compensation medical
bureaus or laboratories and for other laboratories and bureaus shall be made
upon the application form prescribed for the purpose by the chair and shall be
filed with the county medical society, or the workers' compensation committee
of the county medical society, of the county in which such medical bureau or
laboratory is located. Notes
